HEADWORD: Maladroit
<hw>Mal`a*droit"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Malice</er>, and <er>Adroit</er>.]</ety> <def>Of a quality opposed
to adroitness; clumsy; awkward; unskillful.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mal"a*droit`ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mal`a*droit"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

